      • getScanDetailsFor

        @GET
 @Path(value="/org/{orgUuid}/scans/{scanUuid}/details")
 @Produces(value="application/vnd.ilandcloud.api.v0.5+json")
NessusScanDetails getScanDetailsFor(@PathParam(value="orgUuid")
                                                                                                                                                              String orgUuid,
                                                                                                                                                              @PathParam(value="scanUuid")
                                                                                                                                                              String scanUuid)
        Get the scan details for a given organization and a scan UUID. Scan uuid is different than scan id: scan uuid points to a specific scan where scan ID points to the tbplate the scan was run from.
        Parameters:
        orgUuid - org uuid
        Returns:
        list of launched nessus scans for the organization

      • updateScan

        @PUT
 @Path(value="/org/{orgUuid}/scans/{scanId}")
 @Produces(value="application/vnd.ilandcloud.api.v0.5+json")
 @Consumes(value="application/vnd.ilandcloud.api.v0.5+json")
NessusScanUpdate updateScan(@PathParam(value="orgUuid")
                                                                                                                                                                                                         String orgUuid,
                                                                                                                                                                                                         @PathParam(value="scanId")
                                                                                                                                                                                                         int scanId,
                                                                                                                                                                                                         NessusScanSpec spec)
        Update a scan given an organization and the scan ID. The following options are availble to configure:
        • uuid: the uuid for the editor template to use
        • settings.name: the name of the scan
        • settings.description: the description of the scan
        • settings.policy_id: the unique id of the policy to use
        • settings.folder_id: the unique id of the destination folder for thescan
        • settings.scanner_id: the unique id of the scanner to use
        • settings.enabled: if true, the schedule for the scan is enabled
        • settings.launch: when to launch the scan (i.e. DAILY, WEEKLY, MONTHLY or YEARLY)
        • settings.starttime: the starting time and date for the scan (i.e. YYYYMMDDTHHMMSS)
        • settings.rrules: Expects a semi-colon delimited string comprised of three values. The frequency (FREQ=ONCE or DAILY or WEEKLY or MONTHLY or YEARLY), the interval (INTERVAL=1 or 2 or 3 ... x), and the days of the week (BYDAY=SU,MO,TU,WE,TH,FR,SA). To create a scan that runs every three weeks on Monday Wednesday and Friday the string would be 'FREQ=WEEKLY;INTERVAL=3;BYDAY=MO,WE,FR'
        • settings.timezone: The timezone for the scan schedule
        • settings.text_targets: The list of targets to scan
        • settings.file_targets: The name of a file containing the list of targets to scan
        • settings.emails: A comma seperated list of accounts who will receive the email summary report
        • settings.acls: An array containing permissions to apply to the scan
        • settings.use_dashboard: If true, the dashboard will be enabled for this scan
        Parameters:
        orgUuid - org uuid
        scanId - scan id
        spec - specification for updating the scan
        Returns:
        details of the updated scan
